# {{ .ProviderShortName }} Provider

The Check Point SASE Terraform provider manages [Check Point Harmony SASE](https://www.checkpoint.com/harmony/sase/) resources — networks (standard cloud-hosted and enhanced SD-WAN), gateways, IPsec / OpenVPN / WireGuard tunnels, firewall policies, the object library (addresses and services), and applications — through the Harmony SASE Public REST API.

Compatible with **Harmony SASE Public API v2.3.0 and later**. Earlier API versions are not supported by this provider.

## Authentication

The provider authenticates with an API key (JWT). Generate one in the Check Point Infinity Portal under **Harmony SASE → Settings → API Keys**.

The key can be supplied two ways:

| Method | Example |
|---|---|
| Provider attribute | `provider "checkpointsase" { api_key = "..." }` |
| Environment variable | `export CHECKPOINT_SASE_API_KEY=...` |

## Regional endpoints

Set `base_url` (or the `BASE_URL` environment variable) to target your API region. Defaults to the US endpoint when unset.

| Region | URL |
|---|---|
| US (default) | `https://api.perimeter81.com/api/rest` |
| EU | `https://api.eu.sase.checkpoint.com/api/rest` |
| AU | `https://api.au.sase.checkpoint.com/api/rest` |
| IN | `https://api.in.sase.checkpoint.com/api/rest` |

> **Gateway regions vs API regions:** `base_url` selects the control-plane endpoint (one of the four above). Where you actually *deploy* a cloud gateway for a network is a separate dimension covering 50+ locations — discovered at runtime via the `checkpointsase_regions` and `checkpointsase_enhanced_regions` data sources.

## Example usage

```terraform
terraform {
  required_providers {
    checkpointsase = {
      source  = "CheckPoint/checkpoint-sase"
      version = "~> 1.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "checkpointsase" {
  # api_key  = var.api_key                                    # or set CHECKPOINT_SASE_API_KEY
  # base_url = "https://api.eu.sase.checkpoint.com/api/rest"  # optional; defaults to US
}

data "checkpointsase_regions" "all" {}

resource "checkpointsase_network" "example" {
  network {
    name   = "tf-example"
    subnet = "10.0.0.0/16"
    tags   = ["terraform"]
  }

  region {
    cpregion_id = data.checkpointsase_regions.all.regions[0].id
  }
}
```

